<subSubSection id="06AD6573CB411F34FF1DB88A03E4FEFD" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4E0836F8CB411F34FF1DB88A03E4FEFD" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,575]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FF1DB88A003EFF0F" bold="true" box="[151,273,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="89B74D7BCB411F34FDA0B88403ADFF0F" authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[554,642,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FDA0B88403ADFF0F" box="[554,642,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the wing pattern but larger. Two brownish black spots are present under M 
<subScript id="D23334BDCB411F34FF7CB8D601D1FF66" attach="left" box="[246,254,203,217]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="D23334BDCB411F34FEE0B8D6005DFF66" attach="left" box="[362,370,203,217]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">1</subScript>
near the lower angle of the cell on the forewing, instead of big grayish brown patches centered by dark spots as in 
<taxonomicName id="89B74D7BCB411F34FEF9B8FE00E4FF44" authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[371,459,227,251]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FEF9B8FE00E4FF44" box="[371,459,227,251]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the postmedial line is thin and deeply wavy, nearly continuous. In the male genitalia, the two lobes of the uncus are triangular, with the lateral margins oblique, while in 
<taxonomicName id="89B74D7BCB411F34FBCAB91505B8FEA0" authorityName="Watson. So" authorityYear="1957" box="[1088,1175,263,287]" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Tridrepana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="finita">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FBCAB91505B8FEA0" box="[1088,1175,263,287]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">T. finita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the lobes of the uncus are nearly quadrate, with lateral sides nearly erect.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
