<subSubSection id="06AD6573CB411F34FF4FB9A60386FD80" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4E0836F8CB411F34FF4FB9A60386FD80" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,575]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="7CC3EAEACB411F34FF4FB9A60016FE6C" bold="true" box="[197,313,443,467]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="910C885ACB411F34FEF9B9A700FAFE6D" box="[371,469,442,466]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species was dissected by the original authors. In the genitalia slide of the type, the aedeagus has accidentally been placed under the left side of the uncus and is partly covered by the uncus (
<figureCitation id="D68C2A7DCB411F34FAE4B9C20198FDA5" captionStart="FIGURES 59–70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1864,1887]" captionTargetBox="[173,1408,205,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-80@17.[151,1436,193,1799]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 59–70. Male genitalia. 59. T. fulvata brevis; 60. T. arikana arikana; 61. T. arikana emina (Holotype); 62. T. sadana; 63. T. subadelpha sp. nov.; 64. T. adelpha (Holotype); 65. T. hypha (Holotype); 66. T. finita; 67. T. rubromarginata rubromarginata; 68. T. rubromarginata indica; 69. T. thermopasta (Holotype); 70. T. maculosa. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
). Fortunately the features of the aedeagus are recognizable. It is stout and small, lacking a spinose band inside; the cornuti are composed of a bundle of spines.
</paragraph>
